messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: true
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the method-level paths are absolute as written.
- The two handler methods for this path are:
  - @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings", method = RequestMethod.POST) — addNewRingsItem
  - @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings", method = RequestMethod.PUT) — editRingsItem
  These explicit method attributes mean only POST and PUT are implemented for this exact path in the source code.
- No mapping for HEAD, GET, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE, or OPTIONS is present in the code for this path. (Although some frameworks may provide implicit handling for HEAD/OPTIONS at runtime, the requirement was to decide based on the code, so those are marked false.)
- Note: deletion of ring items is implemented at a different path (/printshops/{id}/pricetable/deletering) and uses POST; it does not affect the /printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings path.
